# Ported commands registry — one command name per line.
# The bin/docket dispatcher routes any command listed here to the Python
# entry point (python -m docket) instead of the Bash cmd_* functions.
#
# Rules:
#   - Add a name only after its M0 golden is green on the Python path.
#   - Use the primary command name (not aliases).
#   - Empty = all commands route to Bash (current state during M0–M1).
#
# M3: read-only commands fully ported to Python.
list
info
cost
# M4 wave 1: writer commands — profile, scope, models.
profile
scope
models
# M4 wave 2: delete + channel binding management.
delete
wire
unwire
# M4 wave 3a: edit + snapshot.
edit
snapshot
# M4 wave 3b: logs + workflow.
logs
workflow
# M4 wave 3c: team.
team
# M4 final: auth, context, maintain, keys, add.
auth
context
maintain
keys
add
# M3 T3.4 (late) + M5: doctor, serve.
doctor
serve
# M5 T5.4/T5.3/T5.6 + leftovers.
trace
audit
gates
policies
approve
deny
completions
eval
metrics
help
